        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Shift Back to Society Act of </b><strong>2021</strong></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Education to establish a pilot program that awards matching grants to historically Black colleges and universities to provide educational programs for eligible offenders to facilitate reentry into the community.</p> <p>An eligible offender is a convicted criminal offender who has been released from incarceration for not longer than one year or who is scheduled to be released from incarceration within one year.</p> <p>The Government Accountability Office must report to Congress on the results of the pilot program.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
